PGSScale 0.1.0
Scales PGS subtitles

USAGE:
    pgsscale [FLAGS] [OPTIONS] <INPUT-FILE> <OUTPUT-FILE> --crop-height <PIXELS> --crop-width <PIXELS>

FLAGS:
        --help         Prints help information
    -p, --pq-to-hlg    Enable PQ to HLG conversion of subtitle colors
    -V, --version      Prints version information

OPTIONS:
    -h, --crop-height <PIXELS>    Height to crop each subtitle frame to
    -w, --crop-width <PIXELS>     Width to crop each subtitle frame to
    -r, --ref-white <NITS>        Brightness of the video's reference white level [default: 203]

ARGS:
    <INPUT-FILE>     Input PGS file
    <OUTPUT-FILE>    Output PGS file

This utility will crop PGS subtitles found in Blu-ray discs so that they can match any cropping that has been done to
the main video stream, thereby preventing the subtitles from appearing squished or distorted by the player. Subtitles
from 4K UltraHD discs can optionally be tone mapped to appropriate HLG levels.
